channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: WATCH: Michaelah Montgomery Sets It Off at the Atlanta Trump-Vance Rally
Georgia activist steals the show after being introduced by Trump at Atlanta rally: 'Incredible'
item.description: Former President Trump invited Michaelah Montgomery, a conservative activist, to the stage at his campaign rally, calling her an "incredible" person with a "tremendous future."

item.title: Trump on Debate: Don't Think Harris Will Show Up
item.description: Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump said Vice President Kamala Harris will likely not agree to a debate.

item.title: After Unchecked Waves of Illegal Immigration, the British Are Now Strangers in Their Own Land
Kamala Harris' husband Doug Emhoff admits to extramarital affair that led to breakup of first marriage
item.description: Second gentleman Doug Emhoff on Saturday admitted he had an extramarital affair while married to his first wife years ago after a report from the Daily Mail.

item.title: Trump: Georgia GOP Leaders 'Want Us to Lose'
item.description: Republican presidential nominee pulled no punches against Georgia GOP Gov. Brian Kemp and Attorney General Brad Raffensperger on Saturday night at his Atlanta rally.

item.title: Kamala Campaign Spreads Such an Egregious Tall Tale About Trump Rally, Even NPR Reporter Calls Them Out
JD Vance calls Trump's offer to debate Harris on Fox News ‘masterstroke’
item.description: Republican vice presidential pick JD Vance said Saturday that former President Trump is smart to agree to a debate with Vice President Kamala Harris on Fox News.

item.title: Trump Brings Atlanta Artist Onstage at Rally
item.description: Former President Donald Trump brought a fan on stage during a campaign rally Saturday night in Atlanta.

item.title: Now We Know Who's Going to Play 'Kamala Harris' on SNL Through the 2024 Election
House Armed Services chairman responds after Defense secretary reverses 9/11 plea deal
item.description: House Armed Services Chairman Mike Rogers, R-Ala., said his committee will continue to probe a scrapped Pentagon plea deal with the alleged terrorists behind the Sept. 11 attacks.

item.title: Gov. Kemp Fires Back at Trump
item.description: Republican Georgia Governor Brian Kemp fired back at Donald Trump after the former president criticized his record.

item.title: Why California Can't Afford Its Own Property Insurance Program
Trump Jan. 6 case: Judge sets date for conference to determine steps forward after SCOTUS ruling
item.description: Judge Tanya Chutkan has set an Aug. 16 date for Special Counsel Jack Smith's team and former President Trump's defense attorneys to conference on next steps in Trump's D.C. Jan. 6 case.

item.title: Trump: 'Laken's Blood Is on Kamala Harris' Hands'
item.description: Excoriating the Biden administration's open borders and "migrant crime" wave, Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump said the blood from the death of Laken Riley is "on Kamala Harris' hands."
